In other Essent Group news, CFO Lawrence E. Mcalee, Jr. sold 2,000 shares of Essent Group stock in a transaction that occurred on Friday, July 7th. The stock was sold at an average price of $39.02, for a total transaction of $78,040.00. Following the transaction, the chief financial officer now owns 275,285 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $10,741,620.70. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which is available at this link. Also, CFO Lawrence E. Mcalee, Jr. sold 7,000 shares of Essent Group stock in a transaction that occurred on Friday, June 30th. The stock was sold at an average price of $36.99, for a total value of $258,930.00. Following the transaction, the chief financial officer now directly owns 279,285 shares in the company, valued at approximately $10,330,752.15. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. In the last ninety days, insiders have sold 11,000 shares of company stock worth $412,990. 18.10% of the stock is currently owned by corporate insiders. 
Several hedge funds and other institutional investors have recently made changes to their positions in ESNT. Russell Investments Group Ltd. bought a new position in shares of Essent Group during the fourth quarter valued at $2,440,000. State Board of Administration of Florida Retirement System increased its position in shares of Essent Group by 0.9% in the fourth quarter. State Board of Administration of Florida Retirement System now owns 78,675 shares of the financial services provider’s stock valued at $2,547,000 after buying an additional 700 shares during the period. State Street Corp increased its position in shares of Essent Group by 57.1% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 2,138,526 shares of the financial services provider’s stock valued at $69,221,000 after buying an additional 777,132 shares during the period. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP bought a new position in shares of Essent Group during the fourth quarter valued at $10,106,000. Finally, Martingale Asset Management L P bought a new position in shares of Essent Group during the fourth quarter valued at $270,000. Institutional investors own 85.64% of the company’s stock. 
About Essent Group
Essent Group Ltd. is a private mortgage insurance company. The Company is engaged in offering private mortgage insurance and reinsurance for mortgages secured by residential properties located in the United States. Its products and services include mortgage insurance, contract underwriting, and Bermuda-based insurance and reinsurance.   
